### Generated Test Structure

| Test Class | Tests | Fixture | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `TestSnapshotRestoreRerunOnFailure` | 3 (gating) | `rerun_on_failure_vm_with_snapshot` (class) | Core bug fix: restore completes, no auto-start during restore, VM starts after restore |
| `TestSnapshotRestoreRunStrategies` | 2 x 3 params (Always, Manual, Halted) | `run_strategy_vm_with_snapshot` (class, parametrized) | Regression: restore works for all strategies |
| `TestSnapshotRestoreDataIntegrity` | 2 | `data_integrity_restored_vm` (class) | E2E: pre-snapshot data preserved, post-snapshot data removed |
| `TestMultipleSnapshotRestore` | 2 | `multiple_snapshots_vm` (class) | Multiple snapshots: restore from each completes |

### Key Design Decisions
- **Separate classes per VM fixture** (following GRAVEYARD lesson about class-scoped fixture scheduling)
- **Parametrized class** for regression strategies (Always/Manual/Halted) - pytest runs each parameter sequentially, safe for class-scoped fixtures
- **Inline restore in test body** (matching existing `test_snapshots.py` pattern) - each test creates its own `VirtualMachineRestore` via context manager
- **`_snapshot_vm_for_strategy` helper** - reduces fixture duplication across strategies
- **`ssh_timeout=TIMEOUT_10MIN`** for post-restore VM starts (GRAVEYARD lesson about SSH after disruptive operations)
- **`TimeoutSampler`** for auto-start check polling (GRAVEYARD lesson: never use `time.sleep()` in loops)

